  <prompt>
    Move ComposeWorkspace + its child components + its hooks + its
    types from `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/compose/` into
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Compose.Components/src/widgets/`.
    This unblocks LegalWorkspace's `composeEditor.registration.ts` from
    importing the real widget without inverting the dependency graph
    (matches Calendar Pattern D packaging precedent).

    File moves (source → target):
      src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/compose/
        ComposeWorkspace.tsx
        ComposeWorkspace.types.ts
        ComposeBannerStack.tsx
        ComposeToolbar.tsx
        ComposeEmptyState.tsx
        ComposeConflictDialog.tsx
        hooks/
          useComposeBroadcastChannel.ts
          useComposeCheckoutLifecycle.ts
          useComposeHeartbeatGate.ts
          index.ts
      →
      src/client/shared/Spaarke.Compose.Components/src/widgets/
        (same file structure)

    Update imports in ALL affected files:
      - src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx (imports ComposeWorkspace)
      - Any tests reference ComposeWorkspace/ComposeToolbar/etc.

    Add exports to `@spaarke/compose-components/src/index.ts`:
      export { ComposeWorkspace, ComposeToolbar, ComposeBannerStack,
               ComposeEmptyState, ComposeConflictDialog } from './widgets/...'
      export type { ComposeWorkspaceProps, ComposeToolbarProps, ... }

    Verify:
      1. `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Compose.Components/`
         succeeds (tsc clean; no import cycles)
      2. `npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` succeeds
      3. All tests still pass (npm test in SpaarkeAi + in Spaarke.Compose.Components)
      4. No import from `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/*` back into any shared lib
         (dependency graph unidirectional)

    Keep in mind:
      - ComposeWorkspace has hook dependencies on @spaarke/ai-widgets/events,
        @spaarke/auth, @spaarke/document-operations — these are fine, they're
        shared libs consumed by shared lib.
      - PaneEventBusProvider wrap that App.tsx currently does may move into
        ComposeWorkspace itself (or stay in App.tsx). Decide during refactor.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend packaging engineer familiar with Vite + monorepo dependency
    graphs. Prioritizes zero-regression refactoring; runs full build +
