  <notes>
    Completed 2026-07-01 (~1.5 h; under 3 h estimate).

    Executed:
      - `git mv` for 6 tsx components + ComposeWorkspace.types.ts + 4 hook files
        (3 hooks + hooks/index.ts) + compose-contracts.ts (774 LOC) into
        `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Compose.Components/src/{widgets,widgets/hooks,types}`.
      - Test files relocated to `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/__tests__/compose/`
        (staying in SpaarkeAi jest infra — Events.Components precedent has no
        jest infra either; scope creep to add jest here for R2).
      - 3 relative-path fixes inside moved files: `../../types/compose-contracts`
        → `../types/compose-contracts` (widgets/ is one level deeper than components/).
      - 1 self-import fix: ComposeWorkspace.tsx imported `ComposeEditor` from
        `@spaarke/compose-components` (would circular through the barrel now
        that it's IN the barrel) → changed to `./ComposeEditor`.
      - App.tsx: `./components/compose` → `@spaarke/compose-components` (+
        `./types/compose-contracts` → same package for ComposeDocumentRef).
      - Test imports: use subpath `@spaarke/compose-components/widgets/ComposeToolbar`
        (and same for ComposeConflictDialog) instead of barrel — avoids the
        pre-existing SpaarkeAi jest gap on `@spaarke/ui-components/components/CreateMatterWizard`
        subpath resolution surfaced when tests hit the shared-lib barrel.
      - Deleted stale SpaarkeAi files: `src/components/compose/index.ts` + empty
        dirs (components/compose, components/compose/hooks, components/compose/__tests__)
        + `src/types/compose-contracts.ts` + empty `src/types/`.
      - Updated shared lib `src/index.ts` with 20+ new export lines organized
        into 3 sections: workspace-level widgets, reducer/state types + hooks,
        data contracts (Flows 1-6 + ComposeDocumentRef + ComposeSelection).
      - Added `@spaarke/compose-components` + subpath mapping to SpaarkeAi
        jest.config.ts moduleNameMapper (paralleling existing `@spaarke/ai-widgets`
        + `@spaarke/document-operations` mappings).

